#This readme will show you how to run these programs.
#'>' means the start of the commandline in Unix system.

Excuting run.sh will automatically run all the programs in src, 
including sobel edge detection, mean filter, median filter, laplace sharpen.
>./run.sh

Original images store in directory ./pics/
Generated pictures will be in directory ./pics/result/.


If you would like to run programs individually, follow the instruction below:
1. Sobel Edge Detection
>python sobel.py [original filename] [generated filename]

ex.
>python ./src/sobel.py ./pics/test.tif ./pics/result/sobel_test.png

Others are used in the same way.
